definition.value: A 3-chloroalanine that has R configutation at the chiral centre.
An indanone that consists of 2,3-dihydro-1H-indene substituted by an oxo group at position 1.

A methylpyridine that is 2-methylpyridine substituted by a hydroxy group at C-3, a carboxy group at C-4, and a hydroxymethyl group at C-5. It is the catabolic product of vitamin B6 and is excreted in the urine.
An oxo carboxylic acid that is pyruvic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens has been replaced by an imidazol-5-yl group.
